HEADWORD: Picayune
<hw>Pic`a*yune"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the language
of the Caribs.]</ety> <def>A small coin of the value of six and a
quarter cents. See <er>Fippenny bit</er>.</def> <mark>[Local,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- adj. picayunish; small-minded -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

